President Biden has declared a major disaster in Georgia due to the effects of Hurricane Idalia on August 30, 2023. This declaration makes Federal funding available to affected individuals, counties, and certain nonprofit organizations. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing, home repairs, low-cost loans for property losses, and other recovery programs. Ms. Judy M. Kruger has been appointed to coordinate Federal recovery operations. Damage assessments are ongoing in other areas, and more counties and assistance may be designated later. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance through various channels. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.